OL,7,FIt has been noted that the SNP's
OL,8,FWestminster leader uses a lot of his
OL,9,Ftime at Prime Minister's Questions to
OL,10,Fcriticise Starmer rather than the PM -
OL,11,Fso we asked why.
OL,13,F"Maybe it's because the Labour Party
OL,14,Fhave lost their way a wee bit," he
OL,15,Fsaid.
OL,17,F"In three weeks time, Keir Starmer is
OL,18,Fgoing to be prime minister. The
OL,19,Felection's over, the Tories are
OL,20,Ffinished. Everyone knows he's going to
OL,21,Fbe in power.
